1 subsection may recover actual damages, compensatory damages,
2 attorney’s fees and costs and any other appropriate relief.
3 6. For the purposes of this section, a person or group of
4 persons shall be deemed to engage in paramilitary activity if the
5 person or group of persons knowingly, while acting as part of a
6 private paramilitary organization or in furtherance of any
7 objective of a private paramilitary organization:
8 (a) While armed with a deadly weapon, publicly patrols or
9 drills; or
10 (b) While armed with a dangerous weapon or deadly weapon:
11 (1) Publicly engages in conduct capable of causing physical
12 injury or death;
13 (2) Substantially interferes with the operations of a
14 governmental entity;
15 (3) Unlawfully assumes, exercises or asserts a function,
16 power or duty of a peace officer, state or local governmental
17 official or federal official;
18 (4) Interferes with or impairs or attempts to interfere with
19 or impair the legal rights of another person or group of persons
20 by:
21 (I) Preventing or attempting to prevent the other person
22 or group of persons from engaging in conduct in which the other
23 person or group of persons has a legal right to engage; or
24 (II) Causing or attempting to cause the other person or
25 group of persons to engage in conduct from which the other
26 person or group of persons has a legal right to abstain; or
27 (5) Trains to engage in an activity described in this
28 subsection.
29 7. This section does not apply to:
30 (a) The Armed Forces of the United States, the Nevada
31 National Guard or any regularly organized state militia or
32 unorganized or reserve militia called into service by a state or the
33 United States, including, without limitation, a defense force
34 authorized under 32 U.S.C. § 109(c);
35 (b) A group of persons that:
36 (1) Associates as a military organization solely for
37 historical purposes or fictional performances or parades in public
38 as part of a bona fide veterans’ organization; and
39 (2) Does not carry or use ammunition or explosives;
40 (c) Students in educational institutions where military science
41 is a part of the course of instruction when under the supervision of
42 a military instructor;
43 (d) Members of an organization authorized under state or
44 federal law to provide security services when performing the
45 functions authorized by law;
