2 federal law to provide training in paramilitary operations or law
3 enforcement when:
4 (1) Performing the functions authorized by law; and
5 (2) Under the direction and control of a governmental
6 authority; or
7 (f) Any lawful activity of the Department of Wildlife.
8 8. As used in this section:
9 (a) “Armed forces” has the meaning ascribed to it in 10 U.S.C.
10 § 101(a)(4).
11 (b) “Dangerous weapon” means any weapon, device,
12 instrument, material or substance which, under the circumstances
13 in which it is used, attempted to be used or threatened to be used,
14 is readily capable of causing substantial bodily harm or death.
15 (c) “Deadly weapon” means any instrument which, if used in
16 the ordinary manner contemplated by its design and construction,
17 will or is likely to cause substantial bodily harm or death.
18 (d) “Governmental entity” means an institution, board,
19 commission, bureau, council, department, division, authority or
20 other unit of government of this State, including, without
21 limitation, an agency or political subdivision of this State.
22 (e) “Peace officer” means any person upon whom some or all
23 of the powers of a peace officer are conferred pursuant to NRS
24 289.150 to 289.360, inclusive.
25 (f) “Private paramilitary organization” means an organized
26 body consisting of three or more persons who associate under a
27 structure of command for the purpose of functioning or training
28 to function in a public place as a unit of combat, combat support,
29 law enforcement or security services.
